    public interface HasClassesInSignature
    An interface to an object that has a signature and can provide the classes that are contained in its signature.
    Author:
    Matthew Horridge, Stanford University, Bio-Medical Informatics Research Group, Date: 29/07/2013

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Set<OWLClass> getClassesInSignature()
      Gets the classes in the signature of this object.

    • Method Detail

      • getClassesInSignature

        Set<OWLClass> getClassesInSignature()
        Gets the classes in the signature of this object.
        Returns:
        A set containing the classes that are in the signature of this object. The set is a subset of the signature, and is not backed by the signature; it is a modifiable collection and changes are not reflected by the signature.
